  General methodology: The global approach considered in this     8329 1451
          work is presented in the following paper: Modern        8329 1451
          nuclear data evaluation with the TALYS code system,     8329 1451
          A.J. Koning and D. Rochman, Nuclear Data Sheets 113     8329 1451
          (2012) 2841.                                            8329 1451
                                                                  8329 1451
  MF2:  Resolved resonance range  (RRR)                           8329 1451
       The RRR was generated with TARES-1.31, compiled on         8329 1451
       12-10-2015 11:58:11 PM at Villingen  , Switzerland. The RRR8329 1451
       expands from 0 to 1.364246E+4 eV. A total of               8329 1451
       2 l-values are used and 19 resonances. The resonance       8329 1451
       formalism is multi-level Breit Wigner (MLBW).              8329 1451
       The ladder approach from the CALENDF code is used to       8329 1451
       generate statistical resonances in the unresolved          8329 1451
       resonance range. Therefore, the URR is translated into     8329 1451
       resolved resonance range. Explanations about the method    8329 1451
       can be found in the CALENDF manual: CEA-Report CEA-R-6277  8329 1451
       "CALENDF-2010: User manual" by J.C. Sublet, P. Ribon and   8329 1451
       M. Coste-Delcaux.                                          8329 1451
       The method of creating statistical resonances in the       8329 1451
       URR region is described in: "From average parameters to    8329 1451
       statistical resolved resonances", D. Rochman et al.,       8329 1451
       Annals of Nucl. Ene. 51 (2013) 60.                         8329 1451
       The s-wave average level spacing is 1029 eV and            8329 1451
       the s-wave neutron strength is 6.691e-05 1e-4.             8329 1451
                                                                  8329 1451
  MF32: Covariance file for resonance parameters                  8329 1451
        The compact format is used to represent the covariance    8329 1451
        information on the resonance parameters. Uncertainties    8329 1451
        come from compilations, EXFOR or existing libraries and   8329 1451
        correlations between parameters are obtained following    8329 1451
        the method presented in NIM/A 589 (2008) 85.              8329 1451
