 Nuclear reaction model code EMPIRE-3.2.3 Malta                   8329 1451
 (SVN rev.  4976; source rev.  4972)                              8329 1451
 by M.W.Herman et al [EMP,EMP-man].                               8329 1451
                                                                  8329 1451
 EMPIRE dimensions (dimension.h):                                 8329 1451
  NDNUC= 160  NDEXCLUS= 50  NDEX= 241  NDLW= 100                  8329 1451
  LEVCC= 40  NDLV= 40  NDBR= 40  NDMSCS= 4                        8329 1451
                                                                  8329 1451
 CROSS-SECTION EVALUATION PROCEDURE                               8329 1451
                                                                  8329 1451
 Adopted procedure is based on careful theoretical                8329 1451
 analysis utilizing available experimental data and               8329 1451
 nuclear reaction model calculations.                             8329 1451
                                                                  8329 1451
 This code integrates into a single system a number               8329 1451
 of important modules and features:                               8329 1451
                                                                  8329 1451
 - Spherical and deformed Optical Model including                 8329 1451
   coupled-channels code ECIS06 by J. Raynal                      8329 1451
 - Soft-rotator deformed Optical Model including                  8329 1451
   coupled-channels code OPTMAN by E.Soukhovitskii                8329 1451
   and coworkers                                                  8329 1451
 - Hauser-Feshbach statistical model including                    8329 1451
   width fluctuation correction, and the                          8329 1451
   optical model for fission with partial damping                 8329 1451
 - Quantum-mechanical MSD TUL model (codes ORION &                8329 1451
   TRISTAN by H.Lenske), and MSC NVWY model                       8329 1451
 - Exciton model with Iwamoto-Harada cluster                      8329 1451
   emission and Kalbach systematic angular distr.                 8329 1451
   (code PCROSS by R.Capote et al)                                8329 1451
 - Hybrid Monte Carlo preequilibrium model(M.Blann)               8329 1451
   (code DDHMS by M.Chadwick, mod. by B.V.Carlson)                8329 1451
 - Complete gamma-ray cascade after emission of                   8329 1451
   each particle, including realistic treatment of                8329 1451
   discrete transitions                                           8329 1451
 - Access to OM segment of the RIPL library [RIPL]                8329 1451
 - Built-in input parameter files, such as masses,                8329 1451
   level density, discrete levels, fission barriers               8329 1451
   and gamma strength functions based on the RIPL                 8329 1451
   library [RIPL]                                                 8329 1451
 - Automatic retrieval of experimental data from the              8329 1451
   EXFOR library                                                  8329 1451
 - ENDF-6 formatting (code EMPEND by A.Trkov)                     8329 1451
   coupled to graphical presentation capabilities                 8329 1451
   (code ZVView by V. Zerkin) through the chain of                8329 1451
   PrePro codes by D. Cullen                                      8329 1451
 - ENDF checking codes (CHECKR, FIZCON, PSYCHE)                   8329 1451
 - Highly automated fitting of optical model                      8329 1451
   parameters (by B.V. Carlson)                                   8329 1451
 - KALMAN code for fitting experimental data and                  8329 1451
 - generating covariances                                         8329 1451
 - Support for NJOY                                               8329 1451
                                                                  8329 1451
                                                                  8329 1451
